                    <desc>According to Mochizuki (1999), the composition can be classified into three major sections as follows: (1) a ritual to remove obstacles to a bodhisattva's
            dedication, consisting of (a) confession, (b) generating regret, (c) supplication for protection, and (d) reflecting on the faults and their consequences; (2) taking up virtuous activities
            consisting of (a) naturally virtuous activities in terms of cause-fruit, (b) bodhisattva commitments, and (c) virtues arising from extalted wisdom, and consolidating these into all
            activities; and (3) dedicating the fruits of these to the final goal of complete enlightenment.</desc>
